	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100267757845604><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Backstab</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=107301><span id=Scholar>JimThayner</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>62 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 9th 9:32 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just wanted to tell you that there are stupid people.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here's an example.<br>I was grouping Aviaks in Karanas, and i shout for more in a group.  A rogue responded, and after invitin' him, i commented in fun that "i want to see some good backstabs now" he replied with "I never worked on backstab, its not important" that should have tipped me off to remove him, but i didn't.<br>Well, two kills later, after said i would pull, he goes and pulls three reds on the party.  After yelling at him when i respawned at my bind point, i removed him from the group.  Now, please correct me, but, i think backstab is an important skill (actually, arguably the most important)  Other than the fact that the guy was an idiot, i should have removed him from the group.  My (fatal) mistake.<br>Jim Thayner<br>Jessiicaa, 35 Barbarian Rogue<br>Xegony<br>Shemayl, 22 human paladin<br>Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
