	   <a name=100291030627473></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100291030627473><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100291030627473>RE: Backstab</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100291030627473#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>808 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 12th 2:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.88]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If a rogue is going to give up backstab and piercing then make a warrior. At least that player will live longer.&nbsp;&nbsp;The backstab and piercing weapon is what defines most of what a rogue is to a party.  Ishkur is right - a rogue without backstab is just a ranger without tracking.<br><br>I admit, my 1hs is horrible.  I have done almost nothing but piercing since the beginning.  But my backstab is max'd out for my level.  Max BS damage of 107 is nothing to sneeze at for a level 27 rogue.  Sure I could do better if I had a better weapon than a Crystal Grinder. But I am not a twink so I take what I can scrounge, steal, buy, con, etc.<br><br>Do I miss 1hs? Not really.  With my BS and poisons I manage not to die very often. :-)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
