	   <tr><td colspan=2>LOL nice post. Man oh man, you shoulda realized how dumb she was as soon as you saw her with 2 kodiak claws. I may be wrong, but stats on those are 7dmg 30dly. Even the cheapest piercing weapons (walrus tooth, dragoon dirk, bloodstained fang) have a much better ratio than that! They don't all have a better damage, but as a rogue, especially one who is abandoning backstab, she should have realized that ratio is much more important than damage. <br>To everyone: An interesting thought I had was what if you considered backstab as a third weapon you wielded, and calculated its damage and delay? (Haha! Rogues get triple wield!) In practice and theory, your backstabs will be about 4 times your regular hits, varying on your level, strength, and whatnot. At level 26 with a STR of 123 and a slime coated harpoon with 10 dmg, I get regular hits of 26 and backstabs of 117. That's a backstab-to-regular damage ratio of exactly 4.5. Now I've heard, but I haven't timed it myself, that you backstab every 8 seconds, and that a normal weapon delay is stated in 10ths of a second. That would make my backstab 'weapon' to have a delay of 80.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, with 156 DEX I'm guessing that I'm a little faster than the norm. So I'm estimating my backstab weapon to be a 45 dmg 75 dly weapon. That's a ratio of 1.667. Kick-a$$, ain't it? I'm sorry, but I just love math; I've got to go a step further. Calculating the approximate ratio of ALL weapons together: I get a .793 ratio weapon. Or the equivalent of a 61 dmg, 48 dly weapon. Yes, I am a number cruncher. If you hate number-crunching, then ignore this post and don't flame me. It's just evidence of how important backstab is to a rogue. BTW Ishkur, nice statement about rangers. ;)<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD (Un-retired!)<br>36th Dwarf Rogue<br>Fury Fighters<br>Xegony<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
